The event that cued me into conspiracy theorists was a co-worker woman. She was nice enough for the most part, but she had a weird delusion that the group supervisor was having an affair with another employee in the group. </p><p>
And she was out to prove it. She'd come down to our location with her "proofs". And the employees does there bought into to it. I listened and thought - "what bullshit". I told the folks down there that it was BS, and best to not get involved, and that the woman was kookoo for Co<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
